# AI as a Brainstorming Partner 

#### Sometimes, you might have ideas for a program but are unsure about all the details, such as the target audience or features needed. In these cases, benefiting from brainstorming with someone else can be invaluable. This lesson explores how AI can support you in this step.

<img src="https://images.code.org/f94baf9f962382c7b2c91af53796bea0-image-1712847887689.png" alt="top portion of handout" width="350px" style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0px 35px 40px 20px; border: 2px solid black;">


##Practicing brainstorming with AI

#### Using the LLM of your choice (<a href="https://chat.openai.com/" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ChatGPT</a>, <a href="https://gemini.google.com" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Gemini</a>, or <a href="https://www.bing.com/chat" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Copilot</a>), follow along with the directions on the <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/167P0Kso5w3kvpveY9PKlRwj65Sy0Q7z_o9bbYVlImKE/edit?usp=sharing" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Brainstroming Partner handout</a>. Work through the strategy anticipating how your students might perceive the activity. 


#### For the full student experience, feel free to document your learning in the <a href="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1whiDJn41zHFv9Z4AZEzCQu6LmAXXUE8ZMVshRZI0Lwk/edit?usp=sharing" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">AI Strategies Digital Journal</a>.


